= SDL_GetWindowDisplayMode =
Use this function to fill in information about the display mode used when a fullscreen window is visible on the currently selected display.


== Syntax ==
```c++
int SDL_GetWindowDisplayMode(SDL_WindowID     windowID,
                             SDL_DisplayMode* mode)
```

== Function Parameters ==
{|
|'''windowID'''
|the type used to identify the window
|-
|'''mode'''
|a pointer to the [[SDL_DisplayMode]] to be filled in
|}

== Return Value ==
Returns 0 on success or a negative error code on failure; call [[SDL_GetError]]() for more information.

